VALUES
(41, 4, 18, 42, 8, 14, 14, 'which are sown among thorns', 'Connection of Thorns and Hearing', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of being sown among thorns, highlighting the challenges faced by those who hear the word. The source verse introduces the idea of hearing, while the target passage elaborates on the consequences of being choked by worldly cares.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 4, 18, 40, 13, 22, 22, 'such as hear the word', 'Connection of Thorns and Word', 'Both passages emphasize the impact of thorns on those who hear the word. They highlight how external distractions can hinder spiritual fruitfulness.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 4, 18, 41, 4, 7, 7, 'among thorns', 'Connection of Thorns in Parable', 'Both passages emphasize the presence of thorns that hinder growth. The thorns in both contexts represent obstacles that prevent the word from yielding fruit.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 4, 19, 62, 2, 15, 17, 'the cares of this world', 'Connection of Worldly Concerns', 'Both passages emphasize the dangers of worldly desires and distractions that can lead to spiritual unfruitfulness. Mark 4:19 discusses how the cares of this world can choke the word, while 1 John 2:15-17 warns against loving the world and its lusts.', 'theme', 0.43299999999999994, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 4, 19, 54, 6, 9, 10, 'deceitfulness of riches', 'Connection of Worldly Cares and Riches', 'Both passages emphasize the dangers of wealth and desires, illustrating how they can lead to spiritual unfruitfulness and destruction. The ''deceitfulness of riches'' in Mark parallels the ''love of money'' in 1 Timothy, highlighting the negative impact of materialism on faith.', 'theme', 0.419, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 4, 19, 54, 6, 17, 17, 'deceitfulness of riches', 'Connection Between Wealth and Faith', 'Both passages emphasize the dangers of trusting in riches and the importance of reliance on God. Mark 4:19 warns that the deceitfulness of riches can choke the word, while 1 Timothy 6:17 advises against high-mindedness and trusting in uncertain riches.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 4, 19, 40, 19, 23, 23, 'deceitfulness of riches', 'Connection Between Wealth and Spirituality', 'Both passages emphasize the challenges posed by wealth. Mark highlights how ''the deceitfulness of riches'' can choke the word, while Matthew states that a rich man shall hardly enter into the kingdom of heaven.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 4, 19, 50, 4, 6, 6, 'the cares of this world', 'Concerns of the World', 'This connection highlights the theme of worldly concerns. Mark 4:19 mentions ''the cares of this world,'' while Philippians 4:6 advises against being ''careful for nothing,'' emphasizing reliance on prayer instead.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 4, 19, 60, 4, 2, 3, 'lusts of other things', 'Connection of Worldly Cares and Lusts', 'Both passages emphasize the dangers of worldly cares and lusts that distract from spiritual growth. Mark 4:19 speaks of ''the lusts of other things'' choking the word, while 1 Peter 4:2-3 warns against living according to ''the lusts of men.''', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 4, 19, 42, 12, 29, 30, 'cares of this world', 'Concerns of Worldly Needs', 'Both passages emphasize the distractions of worldly concerns, such as food and drink, which can lead to unfruitfulness in faith. Mark highlights how the ''cares of this world'' can choke the word, while Luke advises against seeking after these same concerns.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 4, 20, 51, 1, 10, 10, 'bring forth fruit', 'Fruitfulness in Good Works', 'Both passages emphasize being fruitful in response to God''s word. Mark highlights the yield of good ground, while Colossians encourages being fruitful in every good work.', 'theme', 0.419, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 4, 20, 42, 8, 15, 15, 'good ground', 'Connection of Good Ground', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of ''good ground'' and the fruitful response to the word. They highlight the importance of receiving the word with a good heart and producing fruit, though Luke adds the aspect of patience.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 4, 20, 43, 15, 4, 5, 'bring forth fruit', 'Fruitfulness in Christ', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of bearing fruit as a result of receiving the word and abiding in Christ. The good ground in Mark produces fruit, while John highlights that abiding in the vine is essential for producing much fruit.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 4, 20, 40, 13, 23, 23, 'sown on good ground', 'Connection of Good Ground', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of ''good ground'' and the fruitful response to the word. They highlight the process of hearing, understanding, and bearing fruit in varying amounts.', 'parallel', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 4, 20, 41, 4, 8, 8, NULL, 'Connection of Fruit Yield', 'Both passages emphasize the yield of fruit from good ground, highlighting the varying degrees of increase. The repetition of ''some thirty, some sixty, and some an hundred'' in both verses reinforces this theme of fruitful response to the word.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 4, 20, 1, 26, 12, 12, 'bring forth fruit', 'Sowing and Harvesting Blessings', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of sowing and receiving a bountiful harvest. Mark speaks of bringing forth fruit, while Genesis describes Isaac receiving an hundredfold in return for his sowing.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 4, 20, 48, 5, 22, 23, 'bring forth fruit', 'Connection of Spiritual Fruit', 'This connection highlights the concept of ''fruit'' in both passages. Mark 4:20 speaks of those who bring forth fruit, while Galatians 5:22-23 lists the specific fruits of the Spirit, emphasizing the positive outcomes of receiving the word.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 4, 21, 40, 5, 15, 15, 'a candle brought to be put under a bushel', 'Light and Visibility of Truth', 'Both passages emphasize the purpose of a candle, highlighting that it is meant to provide light rather than be hidden. This connection illustrates the theme of revealing truth and guidance to others.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 4, 21, 42, 11, 33, 33, 'put under a bushel', 'Light and Visibility Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the purpose of light, illustrating that it should not be hidden but placed where it can be seen. The imagery of a candle and its placement on a candlestick is central to both verses, highlighting the importance of visibility.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 4, 21, 42, 8, 16, 16, NULL, 'Light and Visibility Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the purpose of light, illustrating that it should not be hidden but placed where it can be seen. The imagery of a candle not being covered reinforces the idea of revealing truth and guidance.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 4, 21, 23, 60, 1, 3, NULL, 'Light and Visibility Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of light being revealed. Both passages emphasize the importance of light shining in darkness, suggesting that light should not be hidden but made visible.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 4, 21, 49, 5, 3, 15, NULL, 'Light and Darkness Theme', 'Both passages emphasize the contrast between light and darkness. Mark 4:21 discusses the purpose of light, while Ephesians 5:8-14 calls believers to walk as children of light, revealing truth and goodness.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 4, 21, 46, 12, 7, 7, 'candle brought to be put under', 'Light and Spiritual Gifts', 'This connection highlights the theme of visibility and purpose. In Mark, the candle represents the need to be seen and utilized, while in 1 Corinthians, the manifestation of the Spirit is given for the benefit of all, suggesting that spiritual gifts should also be made evident.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 4, 21, 50, 2, 15, 16, NULL, 'Light and Visibility in Faith', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of shining as lights in the world. Mark highlights the necessity of visibility for a light, while Philippians encourages believers to shine amidst a perverse nation.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 4, 22, 42, 8, 17, 17, 'nothing hid, which shall not be manifested', 'Connection of Hidden Truths', 'Both passages emphasize the revelation of hidden truths, stating that nothing secret will remain undisclosed. The similar phrasing in each verse reinforces the theme of transparency and the inevitability of knowledge coming to light.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 4, 22, 21, 12, 14, 14, 'nothing hid, which shall not be manifested', 'Revelation of Secrets', 'This connection highlights the theme of hidden things being revealed. Both passages emphasize that nothing remains concealed, as God will bring every secret into judgment.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 4, 22, 46, 4, 5, 5, 'nothing hid, which shall not be manifested', 'Revelation of Hidden Things', 'This connection highlights the theme of hidden truths being revealed. Both passages emphasize that nothing concealed will remain secret, as the Lord will bring to light the hidden things.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 4, 22, 19, 78, 2, 4, 'nothing hid, which shall not be manifested', 'Revelation of Hidden Truths', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of revealing truths. Mark speaks of hidden things being manifested, while Psalms discusses not hiding teachings from future generations.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 4, 22, 40, 10, 26, 27, 'nothing hid, which shall not be manifested', 'Revelation of Hidden Truths', 'Both passages emphasize that nothing hidden will remain concealed. They highlight the inevitability of revelation, urging believers to share what they learn openly.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 4, 22, 19, 40, 9, 10, 'nothing hid, which shall not be manifested', 'Revelation of Righteousness', 'This connection highlights the theme of revealing what is hidden. Both passages emphasize the importance of declaring righteousness and truth openly rather than concealing them.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
